    "We considered in the Table, for briefly, the best configuration of parameters (according to the results described in the other subsections, i.e., BPMN as input, BPMN-specific chunking, all-MiniLM-L6-v2 as embedding model).",
    "The table reports, in the first two rows, the results when LLaMA2-13 is used as base LLM.",
    "In this case, the int4 quantization demonstrated superior performance (96,39 percent) not only in terms of reduced computational costs but also in the final accuracy of the BPLLM.",
    "The comparison of Table 4 and the best case reported in Table 3 shows increased accuracy when fine-tuning is performed.",
    "Additionally, in the direction of discovering any potential inverse scaling phenomenon within our task, conducting fine-tuning experiments with the Llama-2-7b-chat-hffoot_12 model under specular conditions."
